{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Problem: JSX Needs One Root"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every JSX expression must compile to a single value — a single "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "React.createElement"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " call. That means you can't return two sibling elements directly:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// ✗ SyntaxError — two adjacent root elements\nfunction UserInfo() {\n  return (\n    <h1>Alice</h1>\n    <p>Frontend Engineer</p>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before Fragments existed, the solution was to wrap siblings in a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<div>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". That works, but the extra "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<div>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " ends up in the DOM — sometimes breaking CSS layout rules or producing invalid HTML."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragments: A Wrapper That Disappears"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A Fragment groups children in JSX without adding a DOM node. React renders its children directly into the parent."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Fragment vs extra div — DOM output comparison showing invalid table structure with div vs valid with Fragment",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two Fragment Syntaxes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shorthand <>...</>"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The short syntax is clean and the default choice in almost all situations:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function UserInfo() {\n  return (\n    <>\n      <h1>Alice</h1>\n      <p>Frontend Engineer</p>\n    </>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Named Fragment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The explicit "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<Fragment>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " syntax is needed when you want to pass a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "key"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " prop — the shorthand doesn't accept props:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { Fragment } from 'react';\n\nconst users = [\n  { id: 1, name: 'Alice', role: 'Admin' },\n  { id: 2, name: 'Bob',   role: 'Viewer' },\n];\n\nfunction UserTable() {\n  return (\n    <table>\n      <tbody>\n        {users.map(user => (\n          // key must be on the outermost element — here that's the Fragment\n          <Fragment key={user.id}>\n            <tr>\n              <td>{user.name}</td>\n              <td>{user.role}</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr className=\"spacer\">\n              <td colSpan={2} />\n            </tr>\n          </Fragment>\n        ))}\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is the only reason to prefer "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<Fragment>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " over "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". In all other cases the short form is cleaner."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Fragments Are Necessary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "There are specific HTML structures where adding an extra DOM node would produce invalid markup. Fragments are the only correct solution in these cases."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Table rows and cells"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// A component that renders two <td> cells together\nfunction TwoColumns({ label, value }) {\n  return (\n    <>                      {/* Fragment — no <div> allowed between <tr> and <td> */}\n      <td>{label}</td>\n      <td>{value}</td>\n    </>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction DataRow({ item }) {\n  return (\n    <tr>\n      <TwoColumns label={item.name} value={item.quantity} />\n    </tr>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Definition lists"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// <dt> and <dd> must be direct children of <dl>\nfunction Term({ word, definition }) {\n  return (\n    <>\n      <dt>{word}</dt>\n      <dd>{definition}</dd>\n    </>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction Glossary({ terms }) {\n  return (\n    <dl>\n      {terms.map(t => <Term key={t.word} word={t.word} definition={t.def} />)}\n    </dl>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CSS flexbox/grid siblings"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a parent container is a flexbox or grid, only its direct children participate in the layout. Wrapping related elements in an extra "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<div>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " creates an unintended flex/grid item:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Parent is display: flex\nfunction Toolbar() {\n  return (\n    <nav style={{ display: 'flex', gap: 8 }}>\n      {/* Without Fragment, extra divs would break the flex layout */}\n      <HomeButton />\n      <SearchButton />\n      <ProfileButton />\n    </nav>\n  );\n}\n\n// Inside SearchButton — Fragment keeps both elements as flex siblings\nfunction SearchButton() {\n  return (\n    <>\n      <button>Search</button>\n      <input type=\"search\" placeholder=\"...\" />\n    </>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragments Are Not Just for Components"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragments can also be used inline anywhere you want to group JSX without a wrapper node — for example, grouping conditionally rendered siblings:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function ArticleBody({ article }) {\n  return (\n    <article>\n      <h1>{article.title}</h1>\n\n      {article.isPremium && (\n        <>                                {/* group two elements together */}\n          <span className=\"badge\">Premium</span>\n          <p className=\"teaser\">Subscribe to read more</p>\n        </>\n      )}\n\n      <p>{article.body}</p>\n    </article>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Returning Multiple Elements from a Function"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A component returns exactly one value from its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "return"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " statement — and that one value can be a Fragment containing any number of children:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function FormField({ label, id, error, children }) {\n  return (\n    <>        {/* one return value — the Fragment itself */}\n      <label htmlFor={id}>{label}</label>\n      {children}   {/* the input, textarea, or select */}\n      {error && <span className=\"error\">{error}</span>}\n    </>\n  );\n}\n\n// Usage\n<FormField label=\"Email\" id=\"email\" error={emailError}>\n  <input id=\"email\" type=\"email\" value={email} onChange={...} />\n</FormField>"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Returning an Array (Advanced)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "React also accepts an array of elements as a render output. This is rare in component returns (Fragments are cleaner), but appears in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "map()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " results and sometimes in render props or utility functions:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Arrays of JSX are valid children\nfunction BreadcrumbList({ crumbs }) {\n  return (\n    <nav>\n      {crumbs.map((crumb, i) => [\n        // Each item in the array needs a key\n        <a key={crumb.href} href={crumb.href}>{crumb.label}</a>,\n        i < crumbs.length - 1 && <span key={`sep-${i}`}> / </span>,\n      ])}\n    </nav>\n  );\n}\n\n// Better written with Fragment to avoid the array + null handling:\nfunction BreadcrumbList({ crumbs }) {\n  return (\n    <nav>\n      {crumbs.map((crumb, i) => (\n        <Fragment key={crumb.href}>\n          <a href={crumb.href}>{crumb.label}</a>\n          {i < crumbs.length - 1 && <span> / </span>}\n        </Fragment>\n      ))}\n    </nav>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragment vs null vs undefined"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a component should render nothing, return "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "null"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — not an empty Fragment. An empty Fragment is valid but communicates nothing about intent:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Renders nothing — correct and explicit\nfunction ConditionalBanner({ show, message }) {\n  if (!show) return null;\n  return <div className=\"banner\">{message}</div>;\n}\n\n// Empty Fragment — valid but unnecessary\nfunction ConditionalBanner({ show, message }) {\n  if (!show) return <></>; // equivalent to null\n  return <div className=\"banner\">{message}</div>;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inspecting Fragments in DevTools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In the browser's Elements panel, Fragments don't appear — their children render directly where they were placed. In React DevTools, Fragments show as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the component tree, so you can see them when debugging."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Patterns That Use Fragments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rendering paired elements"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Icon + label pair used in multiple places\nfunction IconLabel({ icon, label }) {\n  return (\n    <>\n      <span className=\"icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">{icon}</span>\n      <span className=\"label\">{label}</span>\n    </>\n  );\n}\n\n// Usage\n<button>\n  <IconLabel icon=\"⬇\" label=\"Download\" />\n</button>"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Layout components with slots"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// A two-column layout that lets callers provide each column\nfunction SplitLayout({ left, right }) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"split\">\n      <div className=\"left\">{left}</div>\n      <div className=\"right\">{right}</div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// Usage — JSX can be passed as props without wrapping\nfunction Page() {\n  return (\n    <SplitLayout\n      left={\n        <>\n          <h2>Details</h2>\n          <p>Some content here</p>\n        </>\n      }\n      right={\n        <>\n          <img src=\"/chart.png\" alt=\"chart\" />\n          <p>Figure 1</p>\n        </>\n      }\n    />\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Consideration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragments are faster than wrapper elements. React allocates a virtual DOM node for every DOM element — a Fragment skips the allocation entirely. The difference matters in large lists where each row component uses a Fragment instead of an extra "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<div>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// 10,000 rows — the Fragment version allocates ~10,000 fewer virtual nodes\nfunction DataGrid({ rows }) {\n  return (\n    <table>\n      <tbody>\n        {rows.map(row => (\n          <Fragment key={row.id}>  {/* no extra <div> → lighter virtual DOM */}\n            <tr className=\"data-row\">\n              {row.cells.map((cell, i) => <td key={i}>{cell}</td>)}\n            </tr>\n            {row.hasSubRow && (\n              <tr className=\"sub-row\">\n                <td colSpan={row.cells.length}>{row.subRowContent}</td>\n              </tr>\n            )}\n          </Fragment>\n        ))}\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary: When to Use Each Approach"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Situation"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Group children with no layout role for the wrapper"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "<>...</>"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Wrapper needs a key (list rendering)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "<Fragment key={...}>"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Wrapper participates in layout (flex parent, card, etc.)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Real element ("
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "<div>"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": ", "
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "<section>"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": ", etc.)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Component renders nothing"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "return null"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Strict HTML parent-child rules (table, dl, etc.)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "code"
                          }
                        ],
                        "text": "<>...</>"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": " (required)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Fragments in Conditional Rendering" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Fragments shine when you want to conditionally show a group of sibling elements without introducing a wrapper that affects the layout:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "function Notification({ type, title, message, action }) {\n  return (\n    <div className={`notification notification-${type}`}>\n      <strong>{title}</strong>\n\n      {message && (\n        <>                         {/* group message + action without extra div */}\n          <p>{message}</p>\n          {action && (\n            <button onClick={action.onClick}>{action.label}</button>\n          )}\n        </>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Fragments and Early Returns" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Components that use early returns to handle loading and error states also return Fragments when the success state has multiple top-level elements:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "function UserDashboard({ user, loading, error }) {\n  if (loading) return <Spinner />;\n  if (error)   return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;\n  if (!user)   return null;\n\n  // Success state — Fragment groups the multi-element layout\n  return (\n    <>\n      <header>\n        <h1>Welcome, {user.name}</h1>\n        <Avatar src={user.avatarUrl} />\n      </header>\n      <main>\n        <StatsGrid stats={user.stats} />\n        <RecentActivity items={user.recentActivity} />\n      </main>\n    </>\n  );\n}" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "How Fragments Work Internally" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Under the hood, " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "<>" },
          { "type": "text", "text": " and " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "<Fragment>" },
          { "type": "text", "text": " compile to " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "React.createElement(React.Fragment, null, ...children)" },
          { "type": "text", "text": ". The reconciler sees a Fragment node and renders its children directly into the parent fiber without creating a DOM node of its own." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "// What you write\n<>\n  <h1>Title</h1>\n  <p>Body</p>\n</>\n\n// What the compiler generates (new JSX transform)\nimport { jsx as _jsx, Fragment as _Fragment } from 'react/jsx-runtime';\n_jsx(_Fragment, {\n  children: [\n    _jsx('h1', { children: 'Title' }),\n    _jsx('p', { children: 'Body' }),\n  ]\n})" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Keyed Fragments and Reconciliation" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "When React reconciles a list, it uses the " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "key" },
          { "type": "text", "text": " prop to match elements from the previous render to the current render. If you're rendering a list where each item maps to multiple DOM elements, the key must be on the outermost element — which in most cases is a " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "<Fragment key={}>" },
          { "type": "text", "text": ":" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "import { Fragment } from 'react';\n\nconst faqs = [\n  { id: 'q1', question: 'What is React?', answer: 'A UI library.' },\n  { id: 'q2', question: 'What are hooks?', answer: 'Functions for state and effects.' },\n];\n\nfunction FAQ() {\n  return (\n    <dl>\n      {faqs.map(faq => (\n        // key on Fragment — controls how React maps old → new elements\n        <Fragment key={faq.id}>\n          <dt>{faq.question}</dt>\n          <dd>{faq.answer}</dd>\n        </Fragment>\n      ))}\n    </dl>\n  );\n}\n// DOM result:\n// <dl>\n//   <dt>What is React?</dt>\n//   <dd>A UI library.</dd>\n//   <dt>What are hooks?</dt>\n//   <dd>Functions for state and effects.</dd>\n// </dl>" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A Fragment groups JSX children without adding a DOM node — the children appear directly in the parent."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "<>...</>"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for the common case; use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "<Fragment key={...}>"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when you need a key prop (list rendering)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fragments are required wherever extra DOM nodes would violate HTML rules: inside "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "<tr>"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "<dl>"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", or flex/grid containers where an extra element would disrupt layout."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Return "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "null"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when a component should render nothing — not an empty Fragment."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fragments are lighter than DOM elements — they skip virtual DOM node allocation and produce no HTML output."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
